DTEND:20260611T025000Z
SUMMARY:Ragtime
LOCATION:Lincoln Center Theater-Vivian Beaumont, 150 West 65th Street, New York NY 10023
DESCRIPTION:<p>It was the music of something beginning&hellip;<br /><br
  /><em>Ragtime</em> is a sweeping musical adaption of E.L. Doctorow&rsquo;s
  novel that follows three fictional families in pursuit of the American
  Dream at the dawn of the 20th Century: Black pianist Coalhouse Walker, Jr.
  and his beloved Sarah, Jewish immigrant Tateh and his little girl, and a
  wealthy white family led by matriarch Mother. All grasping for the same
  dream, if only they can hold on to it.<br /><br />Featuring a lush score
  by Stephen Flaherty and Lynn Ahrens, a stirring book by Terrence McNally
  and original orchestrations by William David Brohn, all of whom won Tony
  Awards for their work, RAGTIME weaves fictional narratives with real
  historical figures and events, creating a rich tapestry that blurs the
  line between personal struggle and national identity, making history feel
  both intimate and epic.<br /><br />LCT Kewsong Lee Artistic Director Lear
  deBessonet (Tony-nominated for her celebrated 2022 revival of <em>Into the
  Woods</em>) directs a new production, envisioned for the grand Vivian
  Beaumont stage, starring Tony nominee Joshua Henry (<em>Into the
  Woods</em>, <em>Carousel</em>), Olivier and Grammy nominee Caissie Levy
  (<em>Hair</em>, <em>Frozen</em>), and Tony winner Brandon Uranowitz
  (<em>Leopoldstadt</em>, LCT's <em>Falsettos</em>).</p>
END:VEVENT
